This seems a v4 association API bug. Can someone please help to take a look? I think the service has mistaken comany object id for contact id.
API: crm/v4/objects/company/22645422197/associations/contact/52427846997
```request body: [
        {
            "associationCategory": "HubSpot_DEFINED",
            "associationTypeId": 1
        }
]
OkHttp: OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient().newBuilder()
  .build();
MediaType mediaType = MediaType.parse("application/json");
RequestBody body = RequestBody.create(mediaType, "[\n        {\n            \"associationCategory\": \"HubSpot_DEFINED\",\n            \"associationTypeId\": 1\n        }\n]\n");
Request request = new Request.Builder()
  .url("<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v4/objects/company/22645422197/associations/contact/52427846997>")
  .method("PUT", body)
  .addHeader("Content-Type", "application/json")
  .addHeader("Authorization", "Bearer [SECRET]")
  .build();
Response response = client.newCall(request).execute();```

